exercises.name: 21s Bicep Curl
instructions: Perform 7 reps from the bottom to halfway up.
Then, perform 7 reps from halfway to the top.
Finally, perform 7 full-range reps.

exercises.name: Ab Scissors
instructions: Lie on your back with legs straight out.
Lift your heels a few inches off the floor.
Make small, quick, overlapping scissor kicks with your legs.

exercises.name: Ab Wheel
instructions: Kneel on the floor holding the ab wheel.
Slowly roll the wheel forward, keeping your core tight and back straight.
Roll out as far as you can without arching your back, then roll back to the start.

exercises.name: Air Bike
instructions: Sit on the air bike and pedal with your feet while pushing and pulling with your arms.

exercises.name: Arnold Press (Dumbell)
instructions: Sit on a bench holding dumbbells in front of your shoulders, palms facing you.
Press the weights overhead while rotating your palms to face forward at the top.
Reverse the motion on the way down.

exercises.name: Around The World
instructions: Lie on a flat bench with a light dumbbell in each hand.
Start with arms extended to your sides, nearly parallel to the floor.
Bring the dumbbells in a wide, sweeping arc over your head until they touch.
Reverse the arc to return to the start.

exercises.name: Assisted Pistol Squats
instructions: Hold onto a stable object like a pole or suspension trainer.
Balance on one leg and extend the other straight out in front of you.
Lower down into a squat on your standing leg, using the support for balance.
Press back up to the start.

exercises.name: Back Extension (Hyperextension)
instructions: Position yourself on a hyperextension bench, securing your ankles.
With your hands crossed over your chest, bend at the waist until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings.
Raise your torso back up by squeezing your lower back and glutes until your body is in a straight line.

exercises.name: Back Extension (Machine)
instructions: Sit in the back extension machine and secure your legs.
Lean forward and then push back against the pad using your lower back muscles until your back is straight.

exercises.name: Back Extension (Weighted Hyperextension)
instructions: Perform a standard hyperextension while holding a weight plate or dumbbell against your chest.

exercises.name: Band Pullaparts
instructions: Hold a light resistance band with both hands, arms straight out in front of you at shoulder height.
Keeping your arms straight, pull the band apart by squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Return to the start with control.

exercises.name: Battle Ropes
instructions: Hold the ends of the battle ropes and create waves or slams with your arms.

exercises.name: Behind the Back Bicep Wrist Curl (Barbell)
instructions: Hold a barbell behind your back with an overhand grip (palms facing away).
Let the barbell roll down to your fingertips.
Curl your wrists up to lift the barbell.
exercises.media: Behind the Back Bicep Wrist Curl (Barbell).mp4

exercises.name: Behind the Back Curl (Cable)
instructions: Stand facing away from a low pulley cable machine.
Hold the handle with an underhand grip, your arm extended behind you.
Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl the weight forward and up.

exercises.name: Belt Squat (Machine)
instructions: Step onto the platform and attach the belt around your hips.
Stand up to un-rack the weight.
Perform a squat, keeping your torso upright as the weight pulls from your hips.
This removes spinal loading.

exercises.name: Bench Dip
instructions: Sit on the edge of a bench, hands gripping the edge next to your hips.
Slide your butt off the bench with your legs extended.
Lower your body by bending your elbows until they are at about 90 degrees.
Press back up to the start.

exercises.name: Bench Press (Barbell)
instructions: Lie flat on the bench, feet on the floor.
Grip the bar slightly wider than shoulder-width.
Lower the bar to your mid-chest, then press it back up.

exercises.name: Bench Press (Cable)
instructions: Position a bench between two low cable pulleys.
Lie on the bench and grab the handles.
Press the handles up and together over your chest in a pressing motion.

exercises.name: Bench Press (Dumbbell)
instructions: Lie on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand.
Press the dumbbells up over your chest until your arms are fully extended.
Lower them slowly to the sides of your chest.

exercises.name: Bench Press (Smith Machine)
instructions: Position a bench under the Smith machine bar.
Lie down and grip the bar. Un-rack it and lower it to your chest.
Press the bar back up and re-rack.

exercises.name: Bench Press - Close Grip (Barbell)
instructions: Lie on a flat bench and grip the barbell with a shoulder-width or narrower grip.
Lower the bar to your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in.
Press the bar back up, focusing on your triceps.

exercises.name: Bench Press - Wide Grip (Barbell)
instructions: Lie on a flat bench and grip the barbell with a grip wider than shoulder-width.
Lower the bar to your chest. This reduces range of motion but can increase chest activation.
Press the bar back up.

exercises.name: Bent Over Row (Band)
instructions: Stand on the middle of a resistance band with both feet.
Hold the ends of the band, hinge at your hips with a flat back.
Pull the band up towards your torso, squeezing your back muscles.

exercises.name: Bent Over Row (Barbell)
instructions: Hinge at your hips to about a 45-degree angle, holding a barbell with an overhand grip.
Pull the bar to your lower chest, squeezing your back.
Lower with control.

exercises.name: Bent Over Row (Dumbbell)
instructions: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and hinge at your hips with a flat back.
Row the dumbbells up to your sides, keeping elbows close to your body.
Squeeze your back muscles at the top.

exercises.name: Bicep Curl (Barbell)
instructions: Stand holding a barbell with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart.
Keeping your elbows at your sides, curl the weight up.
Squeeze your biceps at the top and lower with control.

exercises.name: Bicep Curl (Cable)
instructions: Attach a straight bar or EZ bar to a low pulley.
Stand facing the machine, grab the bar, and curl it up while keeping your elbows stationary.

exercises.name: Bicep Curl (Dumbbell)
instructions: Stand or sit holding a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward.
Curl the weights up, squeezing your biceps. You can do both at once or alternate.

exercises.name: Bicep Curl (Machine)
instructions: Sit in a bicep curl machine, adjusting the seat so your elbows are aligned with the pivot point.
Curl the handles up towards your shoulders.

exercises.name: Bicep Curl (Suspension)
instructions: Grab suspension trainer handles and lean back until your arms are straight.
Keeping your body straight, pull yourself up by curling your hands towards your shoulders.

exercises.name: Bicycle Crunch Raised Legs
instructions: Lie on your back with legs straight up towards the ceiling.
Perform the bicycle crunch motion, reaching opposite elbow to opposite knee.

exercises.name: Bicycle Crunch
instructions: Lie on your back, hands behind your head, knees bent.
Lift your shoulders off the floor and bring one knee towards the opposite elbow, twisting your torso.
Alternate sides in a pedaling motion.

exercises.name: Bird Dog
instructions: Start on all fours.
Extend one arm straight forward and the opposite leg straight back, keeping your core tight and back flat.
Return to the start and alternate sides.

exercises.name: Body Slams
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Box Jump
instructions: Stand in front of a sturdy box.
Swing your arms and jump explosively onto the box, landing softly.
Step down, don't jump down.

exercises.name: Box Squat (Barbell)
instructions: Place a box or bench behind you.
With a barbell on your back, squat down until you are seated on the box.
Pause briefly, then drive back up to a standing position.

exercises.name: Boxing
instructions: Engage in boxing drills or sparring.

exercises.name: Bulgarian Split Squat
instructions: Place the top of your rear foot on a bench behind you.
Hold dumbbells and lower your body until your front thigh is parallel to the floor.
Drive back up through your front foot.

exercises.name: Burpee Over the Bar
instructions: Place a barbell on the floor.
Perform a burpee on one side of the bar.
After the push-up, jump laterally over the bar and land on the other side. That's one rep.

exercises.name: Burpee
instructions: Start standing, drop into a squat, place hands on the ground.
Kick your feet back to a plank, perform a push-up.
Jump your feet back to the squat position, then jump up explosively.

exercises.name: Butterfly (Pec Deck)
instructions: Sit on the machine with your back flat against the pad.
Place your forearms on the padded levers or grab the handles.
Bring the levers together, squeezing your chest.
Return slowly.

exercises.name: Cable Core Palloff Press
instructions: Stand sideways to a cable machine with the pulley at chest height.
Hold the handle with both hands and step away from the machine.
Press the handle straight out in front of your chest, resisting the rotational pull from the cable.
Bring it back to your chest with control.

exercises.name: Cable Crunch
instructions: Kneel in front of a high pulley with a rope attachment.
Hold the rope on either side of your head.
Crunch your torso downwards, bringing your elbows towards your knees.
Return slowly to the starting position.

exercises.name: Cable Fly Crossovers
instructions: Set two pulleys at chest height.
Grab the handles and step forward.
With a slight bend in your elbows, bring your hands together in front of your chest in a hugging motion.
Squeeze your chest and return slowly.

exercises.name: Cable Pull Through
instructions: Stand facing away from a low pulley with a rope attachment.
Reach between your legs to grab the rope.
Walk forward to create tension, then hinge at your hips, pushing them back.
Drive your hips forward to stand up, squeezing your glutes hard at the top.

exercises.name: Cable Twist (Down to up)
instructions: Set a pulley to a low position.
Stand sideways and grab the handle with both hands.
In a chopping motion, pull the handle up and across your body, twisting your torso.

exercises.name: Cable Twist (Up to down)
instructions: Set a pulley to a high position.
Stand sideways and grab the handle with both hands.
In a chopping motion, pull the handle down and across your body, twisting your torso.

exercises.name: Calf Extensions (Machine)
instructions: This typically refers to a seated or standing calf raise machine. Follow the instructions for that specific machine to press the weight with the balls of your feet.

exercises.name: Calf Press (Machine)
instructions: Sit in a leg press machine and place the balls of your feet on the lower part of the platform.
Press the weight up by extending your ankles.
Lower the weight slowly to feel a stretch in your calves.

exercises.name: Chest Dip (Assisted)
instructions: Use an assisted dip/pull-up machine.
Set the desired assistance weight.
Perform a chest dip with a forward lean.

exercises.name: Chest Dip (Weighted)
instructions: Attach a weight to a dip belt.
Perform a chest dip with a forward lean.

exercises.name: Chest Dip
instructions: Use parallel bars.
Lean your torso forward as you lower your body by bending your elbows.
Go down until you feel a good stretch in your chest, then press back up.

exercises.name: Chest Fly (Band)
instructions: Anchor a resistance band behind you at chest height.
Hold the handles and step forward.
Perform a fly motion, bringing your hands together in front of your chest.

exercises.name: Chest Fly (Dumbbell)
instructions: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other.
With a slight bend in your elbows, lower the weights out to your sides in a wide arc.
Squeeze your chest to bring them back up.

exercises.name: Chest Fly (Machine)
instructions: Same as Butterfly (Pec Deck). Sit in the machine and bring the handles together in front of you.

exercises.name: Chest Fly (Suspension)
instructions: Facing away from the anchor point, hold suspension trainer handles.
Lean forward into a push-up position with arms wide.
Perform a fly motion, bringing your hands together.

exercises.name: Chest Press (Band)
instructions: Loop a resistance band around your back and hold the ends.
Perform a pressing motion, as if doing a push-up.

exercises.name: Chest Press (Machine)
instructions: Sit in the chest press machine with handles at chest level.
Press the handles forward until your arms are fully extended.
Return slowly.

exercises.name: Chest Supported Incline Row (Dumbbell)
instructions: Set a bench to an incline and lie face down with a dumbbell in each hand.
Row the dumbbells up, squeezing your back muscles.
This position helps isolate the back.

exercises.name: Chest Supported Reverse Fly (Dumbbell)
instructions: Lie face down on an incline bench.
With a slight bend in your elbows, raise the dumbbells out to your sides in a reverse fly motion.
Focus on squeezing your rear delts.

exercises.name: Chest Supported Y Raise (Dumbbell)
instructions: Lie face down on an incline bench.
Raise light dumbbells up and out to form a 'Y' shape with your body.
Focus on your upper back and shoulders.

exercises.name: Chin Up (Assisted)
instructions: Use an assisted machine or a band to help you perform chin-ups.

exercises.name: Chin Up (Weighted)
instructions: Add weight using a dip belt or holding a dumbbell between your feet.
Perform chin-ups as normal.

exercises.name: Chin Up
instructions: Hang from a bar with an underhand, shoulder-width grip.
Pull your chin up over the bar.
Lower yourself with control.

exercises.name: Clamshell
instructions: Lie on your side with your knees bent and feet together.
Keeping your feet touching, raise your top knee as high as you can without rotating your hips.
A band can be placed around your thighs for more resistance.

exercises.name: Clap Push Ups
instructions: Perform a standard push-up, but push up explosively enough to clap your hands in mid-air before landing.

exercises.name: Clean and Jerk
instructions: Perform a clean to get the barbell to your shoulders.
From the front rack position, dip your knees and drive the barbell overhead, splitting your legs into a lunge to catch it.

exercises.name: Clean and Press
instructions: Perform a clean to get the barbell to your shoulders.
From the front rack position, perform a strict or push press to lift the weight overhead.

exercises.name: Clean Pull
instructions: Perform the first part of a clean, focusing on the explosive pull from the floor to hip height without catching the bar.

exercises.name: Clean
instructions: An Olympic lift. Start like a deadlift, but as the bar passes your knees, explosively extend your hips and shrug.
Drop under the bar to 'catch' it in a front squat position.

exercises.name: Concentration Curl
instructions: Sit on a bench, lean forward, and brace your elbow against your inner thigh.
Curl the dumbbell up, focusing on a strong bicep contraction.

exercises.name: Cross Body Hammer Curl
instructions: Stand holding dumbbells with a neutral (hammer) grip.
Curl one dumbbell up and across your body toward the opposite shoulder.
Alternate arms.

exercises.name: Crunch (Machine)
instructions: Sit in the crunch machine and grab the handles or place arms on the pads.
Crunch your torso forward against the resistance.

exercises.name: Crunch (Weighted)
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Crunch
instructions: Lie on your back with knees bent.
Lift your shoulders off the floor, contracting your abs.
Keep your lower back on the floor.

exercises.name: Curtsy Lunge (Dumbbell)
instructions: Holding dumbbells, step one leg behind and across the other, as if doing a curtsy.
Lower down into a lunge, then return to the start.

exercises.name: Dead Bug
instructions: Lie on your back with arms extended up and knees bent at 90 degrees.
Slowly lower one arm and the opposite leg toward the floor, keeping your core engaged and lower back pressed down.
Return to the start and alternate sides.

exercises.name: Dead Hang
instructions: Simply hang from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip.
This is great for grip strength and decompressing the spine.

exercises.name: Deadlift (Band)
instructions: Stand on a resistance band and hold the ends.
Hinge at your hips and perform a deadlift motion against the band's resistance.

exercises.name: Deadlift (Barbell)
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Deadlift (Dumbbell)
instructions: Hold a dumbbell in each hand in front of you.
Hinge at your hips with a flat back, lowering the dumbbells toward the floor.
Drive your hips forward to stand back up.

exercises.name: Deadlift (Smith Machine)
instructions: Stand in a Smith machine and perform a deadlift motion. The fixed path can help with form but engages fewer stabilizer muscles.

exercises.name: Deadlift (Trap bar)
instructions: Stand inside a trap bar and grip the handles.
Perform a deadlift motion. This variation is often easier on the lower back.

exercises.name: Deadlift High Pull
instructions: Perform a deadlift, but as you stand up, continue the momentum by pulling the bar up to your chest, leading with your elbows.

exercises.name: Decline Bench Press (Barbell)
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Decline Bench Press (Dumbbell)
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Decline Bench Press (Machine)
instructions: Use a decline chest press machine, pressing the handles forward and up.

exercises.name: Decline Bench Press (Smith Machine)
instructions: Position a decline bench under a Smith machine and perform a decline press.

exercises.name: Decline Chest Fly (Dumbbell)
instructions: Lie on a decline bench and perform a dumbbell fly, focusing on the lower chest.

exercises.name: Decline Crunch (Weighted)
instructions: Hold a weight plate on your chest while performing a decline crunch.

exercises.name: Decline Crunch
instructions: Lie on a decline bench, securing your feet.
Perform a crunch motion. The decline adds difficulty.

exercises.name: Decline Push Up
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Diamond Push Up
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Downward Dog
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Drag Curl
instructions: Hold a barbell with an underhand grip.
Instead of curling in an arc, drag the bar up your torso, pulling your elbows back.
This focuses on the peak contraction of the bicep.

exercises.name: Dragon Flag
instructions: Lie on a bench and grip it behind your head.
Lift your entire body off the bench, keeping it straight.
Slowly lower your body without touching the bench until the next rep.

exercises.name: Dragonfly
instructions: A variation of the Dragon Flag where you open and close your legs at the top of the movement.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Row
instructions: Place one knee and hand on a bench.
Hold a dumbbell in the opposite hand and row it up to your side, squeezing your back.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Snatch
instructions: Start with a dumbbell on the floor between your feet.
In one explosive movement, pull the dumbbell from the floor straight overhead, dropping under it slightly to catch it.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Squeeze Press
instructions: Lie on a bench holding two dumbbells pressed together over your chest.
Lower them to your chest and press back up, maintaining constant pressure between the dumbbells.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Step Up
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Elbow to Knee
instructions: Similar to a bicycle crunch, but often performed more slowly and deliberately.

exercises.name: Elliptical Trainer
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: EZ Bar Biceps Curl
instructions: Hold an EZ bar with an underhand grip.
Perform a bicep curl. The angled bar can be more comfortable on the wrists.

exercises.name: Face Pull
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Farmers Walk
instructions: Hold a heavy dumbbell or kettlebell in each hand.
Walk for a set distance or time, maintaining an upright posture and tight core.

exercises.name: Feet Up Bench Press (Barbell)
instructions: Perform a barbell bench press with your feet on the bench.
This removes leg drive and forces your upper body to do more work.

exercises.name: Fire Hydrants
instructions: Start on all fours.
Keeping your knee bent, lift one leg out to the side, activating your glute medius.

exercises.name: Floor Press (Barbell)
instructions: Lie on the floor and perform a bench press motion.
The range of motion is shorter, focusing on the lockout and triceps.

exercises.name: Floor Press (Dumbbell)
instructions: Lie on the floor and perform a dumbbell press.
The floor stops your elbows, reducing shoulder strain.

exercises.name: Floor Triceps Dip
instructions: Sit on the floor with knees bent and hands behind you.
Lift your hips off the floor and bend your elbows to lower your body.
Press back up with your triceps.

exercises.name: Flutter Kicks
instructions: Lie on your back and lift your legs slightly.
Perform small, quick up-and-down kicks.

exercises.name: Frog Jumps
instructions: Start in a deep squat position.
Jump forward explosively, landing back in a deep squat.

exercises.name: Frog Pumps (Dumbbell)
instructions: Lie on your back with the soles of your feet together and knees out wide.
Place a dumbbell on your hips.
Perform small, quick hip thrusts in this position.

exercises.name: Front Lever Hold
instructions: A gymnastics move. Hang from a bar and hold your body horizontally, facing up.

exercises.name: Front Lever Raise
instructions: From a dead hang, pull your body up into a front lever position.

exercises.name: Front Raise (Band)
instructions: Stand on a resistance band and hold the handles.
Raise your arms straight out in front of you to shoulder height.

exercises.name: Front Raise (Barbell)
instructions: Hold a barbell with an overhand grip.
Raise the bar to shoulder height with straight arms.

exercises.name: Front Raise (Cable)
instructions: Stand facing away from a low pulley with a handle.
Raise your arm straight out in front of you.

exercises.name: Front Raise (Dumbbell)
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Front Raise (Suspension)
instructions: Facing away from the anchor point, lean back and raise your arms straight out in front of you.

exercises.name: Front Squat
instructions: Hold a barbell across the front of your shoulders (front rack position).
Perform a squat, keeping your torso upright.

exercises.name: Full Squat
instructions: Same as a Barbell Back Squat, emphasizing a deep range of motion (ass-to-grass).

exercises.name: Glute Bridge
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Glute Ham Raise
instructions: Use a GHD machine.
Lower your torso towards the floor, then pull yourself back up using your hamstrings and glutes.

exercises.name: Glute Kickback (Machine)
instructions: Position yourself in a glute kickback machine.
Press your leg back against the pad, squeezing your glute.

exercises.name: Glute Kickback on Floor
instructions: Start on all fours.
Kick one leg back and up, squeezing the glute.

exercises.name: Goblet Squat
instructions: Instructions need to be added for this exercise.

exercises.name: Good Morning (Barbell)
instructions: Place a barbell on your back like a squat.
Hinge at your hips, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent, until your torso is parallel to the floor.
Return to the start by squeezing your glutes and hamstrings.

exercises.name: Gorilla Row (Kettlebell)
instructions: Place two kettlebells between your feet.
Hinge at the hips and row one kettlebell up while the other hand supports you on the other kettlebell. Alternate sides.

exercises.name: Hack Squat (Machine)
instructions: Use a hack squat machine, placing your back against the pad.
Perform a squat, focusing on the quadriceps.

exercises.name: Hack Squat
instructions: A barbell variation where the bar is held behind the legs.
Perform a squat motion. This is an advanced movement.

Perform a hammer curl.

Push.name: Arm Circles
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.
Extend your arms to the sides.
Make small circles, gradually increasing to large circles.
Perform for 30 seconds forward, then 30 seconds backward.

Push.name: Torso Twists
instructions: Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder-width, knees slightly bent.
Hold your arms out or cross them over your chest.
Gently twist your torso from side to side.
Perform for 30-60 seconds.

Push.name: Dynamic Chest Stretches
instructions: Stand tall.
Swing both arms outwards and backwards, feeling a stretch in your chest.
Return arms to the front, crossing them over each other.
Repeat for 10-15 repetitions.

Pull.name: Cat-Cow
instructions: Start on your hands and knees.
Inhale as you drop your belly towards the mat (Cow).
Exhale as you round your spine upwards (Cat).
Repeat for 10-15 repetitions.

Pull.name: Scapular Pull-ups
instructions: Hang from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip.
Without bending your arms, pull your shoulder blades down and together.
Hold for a second, then relax.
Repeat for 8-12 repetitions.

Pull.name: Band Pull-Aparts
instructions: Hold a light resistance band with both hands, shoulder-width apart.
Keeping your arms straight, pull the band apart by squeezing your shoulder blades.
Return to the start with control.
Repeat for 15-20 repetitions.

Legs.name: Front-to-back Leg Swings
instructions: Hold onto a stable surface for balance.
Swing one leg forward and backward in a controlled motion.
Keep your core engaged and torso upright.
Perform 10-15 swings per leg.

Legs.name: Side-to-side Leg Swings
instructions: Face a stable surface and hold on for balance.
Swing one leg out to the side, then across the front of your body.
Keep the movement controlled.
Perform 10-15 swings per leg.

Legs.name: Side Lying Twists
instructions: Lie on your side with your knees bent at 90 degrees.
Extend your top arm and rotate your torso, trying to touch your top shoulder blade to the floor.
Follow your hand with your eyes.
Perform 8-10 twists per side.

Legs.name: Step Throughs
instructions: Start in a push-up position.
Bring your right foot forward and place it outside your right hand, sinking your hips.
Hold for a moment, then step back to the start.
Repeat with the left leg.
Alternate for 5-8 repetitions per side.

General.name: Downward Dog
instructions: Start on hands and knees.
Lift your hips up and back to form an inverted V shape.

General.name: Stretching
instructions: Perform various dynamic or static stretches targeting major muscle groups.

General.name: Warm Up
instructions: Perform light cardio and dynamic stretches to prepare for your workout.

General.name: Yoga
instructions: Follow a yoga routine to improve flexibility and mindfulness.

General.name: Pilates
instructions: Follow a Pilates routine to improve core strength and stability.

General.name: Aerobics
instructions: Follow an aerobics routine.

General.name: Air Bike
instructions: Sit on the air bike and pedal with your feet while pushing and pulling with your arms.

General.name: Battle Ropes
instructions: Hold the ends of the battle ropes and create waves or slams with your arms.

General.name: Boxing
instructions: Engage in boxing drills or sparring.

General.name: Climbing
instructions: Climb on a rock wall or similar structure.

General.name: Cycling
instructions: Ride a stationary or outdoor bicycle.

General.name: Elliptical Trainer
instructions: Use an elliptical machine for a low-impact cardio workout.

General.name: HIIT
instructions: Perform high-intensity interval training, alternating between intense bursts of activity and short recovery periods.

General.name: Hiking
instructions: Walk on outdoor trails, often with elevation changes.

General.name: Jump Rope
instructions: Jump over a rope as it passes under your feet.

General.name: Rowing Machine
instructions: Use a rowing machine for a full-body cardio workout.

General.name: Running
instructions: Run outdoors or on a treadmill.

General.name: Skating
instructions: Ice skate or rollerblade.

General.name: Skiing
instructions: Ski downhill or cross-country.

General.name: Snowboarding
instructions: Ride a snowboard down a snow-covered slope.

General.name: Spinning
instructions: Participate in a group indoor cycling class.

General.name: Sprints
instructions: Run at maximum speed for short distances.

General.name: Stair Machine (Floors)
instructions: Use a stair-climbing machine, tracking floors climbed.

General.name: Stair Machine (Steps)
instructions: Use a stair-climbing machine, tracking steps taken.

General.name: Swimming
instructions: Swim laps in a pool or open water.

General.name: Treadmill
instructions: Walk, jog, or run on a treadmill.

General.name: Walking
instructions: Walk at a steady pace indoors or outdoors.
